radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases demonstrate mild dependent atelectatic changes. The appendix is fluid filled and distended measuring up to 13 mm with hyperemia and surrounding inflammation and free fluid. A 9 x 6 mm hyperdense focus likely represents an appendicolith. The appendix is retrocecal. A small amount of free fluid is noted within the pelvis. Several ileocolic lymph nodes are likely reactive.
